name: Appetite Classic

reviews.review_text:
Enjoy a breezy afternoon sipping on some beers or cocktails and Goan food on the first floor of this restaurant.

With the beautiful view of the town below, this probably is the selling point of this restaurant.

The food is good but the view is better.
Just spend a lazy afternoon here and enjoy your food.

We wanted to go for a rainy Sunday afternoon thali and had heard good things about this place. Unfortunately they don’t serve their thalis on Sunday.
We stayed for lunch anyway.

The service was quite relaxed in the typical Goan style, but it was worth the wait with the amazing prawn curry and prawn rava fry which were just outstanding and our favourites!

We also had silver fish fry, chinak fry -‘d surmai fry, along with some fish caldin.
These were all good, but not the best we’ve ever eaten.

What makes this place worth it is the prawn curry of course, but also the stunning views! It is in a gorgeous green location overlooking trees and was absolutely perfect in the monsoon!

They also have an AC section which would be great during the summers, but then you lose the views.

It’s a good option if you’re in mapusa and want a nice open space instead of being in a cramped restaurant.

The food was decent but the service was very slow . The waiter didn't even clear our plate once done with starters. We came through swiggy dine out and it was mentioned with free drink but the restaurant disagreed and caused a problem. The worst part was the serradura desert i had. It was just full of cream and only pinch of biscuit powder. It was very upsetting. Please improve on these points. Would love to change my reviews about it in the near future. Thank you.

description:
**Appetite Classic: A Hidden Gem with Scenic Vistas and Flavorful Fare**

Nestled in the charming locale of Tivim, Appetite Classic boasts a respectable rating of **3.8** based on **1,162 reviews**, making it a notable spot among locals and visitors alike. The restaurant frequently garners attention for its **fish dishes** (21 mentions), specifically the seafood curry varieties, as well as the relaxed ambiance perfect for a **dinner** outing (18 mentions). Frequent references to **quantity** (15 mentions) indicate a generous serving approach, coupled with a commendable focus on **food and service** (12 mentions), emphasizing the restaurant's dual commitment to culinary satisfaction and guest experience.

**Ambiance & Design**

Upon entering Appetite Classic, guests are greeted by a captivating décor that harmonizes with the natural beauty of its surroundings. The first-floor dining area offers a breathtaking **view of the lush landscape**, and the arrangement of tables allows diners to soak in the scenery while enjoying their meals. Complemented by soft lighting and a breezy atmosphere, the restaurant exudes a tranquil vibe ideal for leisurely afternoons or intimate dinners. Customers have noted the appealing layout, especially during the monsoon seasons when the greenery thrives in vibrant shades—a backdrop perfect for a cozy, relaxed dining experience.

**Menu & Culinary Experience**

Appetite Classic shines brightest with its seafood specialties. Patrons rave about the **prawn curry**—a standout dish that has won many hearts due to its robust flavors—and the **prawn rava fry**, which is equally celebrated for its delightful crunch. Other favored items include **silver fish fry** and the **surmai fry**, showcasing a variety of preparation styles that highlight the region's culinary richness. The **fish caldin**, though appreciated, hasn't received as much acclaim, suggesting that while the menu is diverse, certain dishes significantly outshine others.

Reviewers have mentioned the experience of dining at Appetite Classic is elevated by the substantial portion sizes that ensure value. Vegetarians may find options to suit their tastes as well, though the restaurant is particularly renowned for its seafood offerings. Some photos captured by guests have showcased the beautifully plated dishes, featuring vibrant colors that reflect the fresh ingredients used, making for a feast that delights both the palate and the eyes.

**Customer Experience & Service**

In line with Goa’s laid-back culture, the service at Appetite Classic can be characterized as relaxed—perhaps a bit too slow for some tastes. Guests have noted that while the service is friendly, it occasionally leaves much to be desired, particularly during busy hours. There have been reports of erratic service experiences, such as delays in clearing plates and discrepancies with orders, which suggest that consistency in service could be an area for improvement. However, the overall warm demeanor of the staff often helps to counterbalance these hiccups, making guests feel at home.

Guests are advised to check reservation policies in advance, especially during peak dining hours or weekends, as walk-in availability may vary.

**Popularity & Reviews**

The restaurant's popularity is evident in its swelling review count and positive mentions across numerous platforms. Although several reviews highlight minor service concerns, the overall sentiment leans towards appreciation for the food quality and the stunning setting. Visitors frequently emphasize the **atmosphere** as a key draw, suggesting that, when in Mapusa, Appetite Classic is a preferred destination for those wishing to escape the hustle of typical eateries in favor of open spaces and picturesque views.

**Utilizing Visual Content**

Customer photos corroborate the restaurant’s appeal, offering glimpses into the comfortably spaced dining setup and the stunning vistas that greet diners. Images of vibrant dishes like the golden-fried prawns and the rich-looking curries vividly illustrate the culinary artistry underway at Appetite Classic, while also showcasing the enchanting greenery that frames the restaurant’s atmosphere.

In conclusion, Appetite Classic presents an experience that appeals to those looking to indulge in delectable seafood while soaking in beautiful views. With continued improvement in service consistency, this hidden gem could easily elevate its status in the dining scene of Tivim, making it a must-visit for both locals and travelers exploring Goa’s culinary landscape.
